Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:262492,265028}{\i1}Soon, the city of Paris\Nwas about to become a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:266162,271401}{\i1}In fear of losing homes and properties\Nafter being involved in battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.40,0:04:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:271401,274270}{\i1}the rich and powerful\Nstarted to seek shelter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.27,0:04:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:274270,279476}{\i1}and one after another\Nmigrated to the city of Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.91,0:04:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:280910,284814}Mommy,\Nwhere is everyone going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:284814,288651}The war is about to begin.\NThey're running away to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.65,0:04:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:288651,290587}Are we going to move, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.58,0:04:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:290587,292722}I don't really want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.28,0:04:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:293289,297694}Even if we escaped,\Nwe don't have any villas to hide in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.46,0:05:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:298461,301965}There is no place for us\Noutside of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.96,0:05:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:301965,306469}These people live in a world\Nthat is entirely different from ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.46,0:05:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:306469,310807}They don't care at all\Nwhat happens to this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.10,0:05:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:311107,312275}{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:312275,319516}{\i1}Only a limited number of people\Nhad a place to escape from war.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.51,0:05:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:319516,321818}{\i1}The Rostain family\Nwas among the lucky ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.55,0:05:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:326556,328658}Quick, quick, quick!\NNo time for dilly-dallying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.65,0:05:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:328658,331227}The Prussian army\Nis just around the corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.86,0:05:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:331861,335064}Remember,\Nonly the nobles' belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.27,0:05:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:340270,342572}I don't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.57,0:05:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:342572,343706}What a drag!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.84,0:05:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:345842,348478}I guess it's time to say goodbye\Nto this house for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.47,0:05:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:348478,349212}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.01,0:05:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:352015,353783}Andréa… It's Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.22,0:06:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:362225,363760}I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.06,0:06:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:367063,368631}Outta my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.76,0:06:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:369766,372202}What… What are you doing, young lady?\NStop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.20,0:06:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:372202,375104}Now is not the time for the lectures.\NIt's Andréa! It's Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.37,0:06:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:375371,376806}Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.80,0:06:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376806,377807}Who do we have here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.80,0:06:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:377807,379175}Andréa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.17,0:06:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:379175,381778}Andréa… Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.37,0:06:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382378,385582}Ms. Isabelle…\NYou're just too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.21,0:06:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:386216,388318}Hello, Jeanne. I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.98,0:06:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:388985,391087}Young master!\NWhat am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.08,0:06:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:391087,395158}Young master is here.\NMaster! Milady! Mr. Andréa is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.15,0:06:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395158,396259}How have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.25,0:06:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:396259,398561}Stupid, stupid brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.56,0:06:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:398561,401064}Do you have any idea\Nhow worried I was?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.06,0:06:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:401064,404567}Hey, hey, Isabelle.\NWhat's with this messy reception?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.56,0:06:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:404567,408338}Haven't you made your debut\Nin high society and become a lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.77,0:06:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:409772,413176}That's right. I'm a lady now.\NIsn't that right, Mr. Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.44,0:06:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:413443,416746}Yes. You made\Nan excellent lady that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:451881,457787}It is a pity that we must part\Njust after our family has finally reunited.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.25,0:07:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:458254,462025}Father, you'll be safe\Nas long as you stay in Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:462025,464961}When we know\Nthat our family is safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.96,0:07:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:464961,467664}we'll feel much more confident\Non the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.66,0:07:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:467664,470500}Right.\NBut don't do anything reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.50,0:07:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:470500,472068}I understand. We won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.06,0:07:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:472068,474337}Our goal is not to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.33,0:07:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:474337,476406}It is to protect Paris to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.67,0:08:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:477674,481444}Apropos, Victor. You will not be able\Nto see Geneviève for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:481444,486249}I was hoping you could\Nget married, even if just in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.68,0:08:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:486683,489085}Marriage? Now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.28,0:08:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:489285,490954}Yes, that's exactly what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.95,0:08:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:490954,493723}Young people have a tendency\Nof making fools of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:493723,496225}If you get married,\Nyou will start to be cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.22,0:08:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:496225,498861}And caution in war\Nis at a premium.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.06,0:08:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:499062,501898}Victor, now might be\Nactually the best time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.89,0:08:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:501898,503132}What will you do
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.13,0:08:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:503132,506336}if your betrothed has a little fun\Non the side behind your back?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.53,0:08:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:506536,510073}But I am going to fight\Nat the front line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.07,0:08:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:510073,512442}If something were\Nto happen to me…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:512442,515845}Victor. I am a French man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.84,0:08:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:515845,520450}Do you think a French soldier's wife is afraid\Nthat her husband will die protecting France?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.45,0:08:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:520450,523586}I don't remember\Nraising my daughter in such a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:523586,526122}Women do change their mind\Nabout such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.32,0:08:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:528324,531627}{\i1}Isabelle felt uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.62,0:08:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:531627,534197}{\i1}Isabelle knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.19,0:09:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534197,540370}{\i1}She knew that Geneviève\Nhad another lover besides Victor… Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.11,0:09:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:556119,557420}Isabelle…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.42,0:09:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:557420,559222}I can not help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.85,0:09:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:559856,561424}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.42,0:09:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:561424,563426}Poor Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.59,0:09:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:565595,566763}{\i1}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.76,0:09:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:566763,568765}{\i1}Why are you silent?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.76,0:09:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:568765,570600}{\i1}You're such a coward, sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.60,0:09:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:570600,572969}{\i1}Why don't you say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.93,0:09:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:573936,580943}{\i1}Geneviève's mind was now full of thoughts\Nabout her piano teacher, Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.14,0:10:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:615144,618381}You're the daughter\Nof a great landowner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.38,0:10:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:618381,622318}And I'm… a pianist who lives\Nin town on the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.31,0:10:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:622318,624921}The worlds we live in\Nare too far apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.92,0:10:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:624921,627657}I don't have what it takes\Nto make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.65,0:10:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:627657,632061}You coward! I will…\NI will follow you wherever you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.06,0:10:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:632061,633830}There's nothing we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:633830,636065}Geneviève…\NThere's nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.46,0:10:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:639469,642538}A wedding only in writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.53,0:10:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:642538,644340}I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.34,0:10:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:644340,645842}I take your daughter as my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.07,0:10:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:647076,649812}You finally made up your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.11,0:10:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:650113,653182}Congratulations, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.18,0:10:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:653182,655885}Very well.\NLet us have a toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:655885,656986}Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.98,0:10:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:656986,659722}I know I made you wait\Na bit too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.72,0:11:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:659722,663826}But please believe me, I have been\Nthinking only of you all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.32,0:11:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:665328,668264}Geneviève.\NYou will marry me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.44,0:11:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679442,682578}{\i1}Isabelle, who knew\Nabout Geneviève's feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:682578,685615}{\i1}only stood there\Nand watched this scene in silence.
Comment: 0,0:11:28.85,0:11:28.85,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:688851,688851}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:11:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:712008,716379}The elite are all fleeing to their\Nnice safe properties in Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.37,0:11:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:716379,718881}Must be nice,\Nhaving a place to escape to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.88,0:12:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:718881,722685}What about us?\NWhere are we going to escape to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.68,0:12:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:722685,724620}Escape?\NYou better be kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:724620,728591}I was born and raised in this town.\NI am a proud Parisian.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.59,0:12:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:728591,730927}I won't let anybody\Nhave our city.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.92,0:12:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:730927,734163}Damn right!\NI'm not moving an inch from this city!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:734564,738000}I'll say one thing. I won't stay idle\Nwhen the Prussian army comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.23,0:12:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:738234,741837}Music to my ears. I'll fight\Nby your side when the time comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.07,0:12:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:742071,743306}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.14,0:12:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:744140,746943}Hey, everybody!\NWe are Parisians!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.94,0:12:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:746943,748678}Paris is our city!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.11,0:12:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:749111,750046}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.34,0:12:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:750346,752548}Who is going to defend our city?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:752548,753382}Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.38,0:12:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:753382,754317}The army?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.31,0:12:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:754317,755384}The politicians?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:755384,756319}The aristocrats?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.31,0:12:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:756319,757887}No. It'll be us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.88,0:12:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757887,759288}It'll be us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.28,0:12:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:759288,761857}We'll protect our city\Nby ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.85,0:12:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:761857,763025}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.02,0:12:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:763025,765027}We will be the ones\Nwho protect Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.02,0:12:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:765027,766062}It'll be us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.06,0:12:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:766062,767163}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.16,0:12:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:767163,768030}We'll defend it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.03,0:12:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:768030,769098}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.09,0:12:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769098,769966}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.96,0:12:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769966,771033}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.03,0:12:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771033,771767}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.76,0:12:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771767,773402}– Defend Paris!\N– Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.40,0:12:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:773402,775905}Defend Paris!\NWe'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.90,0:12:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:775905,777406}We'll defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.40,0:12:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:777406,778975}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:779842,781811}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.81,0:13:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:781811,783646}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.64,0:13:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:783646,785114}{\fad(0,1468)}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.38,0:13:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:785381,787350}Exciting times, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.98,0:13:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:787984,791554}Yes. These are the real feelings\Nof those truly living in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.48,0:13:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:792488,797660}There is no love for Paris among the people\Nwho leave it and flee to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:797960,801130}I heard that the Rostain family\Nis evacuating there as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.13,0:13:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:801130,802131}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.26,0:13:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:804267,807003}Must be nice, not having\Nto worry about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.07,0:13:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:811073,814210}Ordinary people have it\Nworse than ever these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.21,0:13:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:814210,815745}I'm a bit jealous of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.24,0:13:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:816245,818347}Cut it. Leave Geneviève out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.34,0:13:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:818347,820716}A relationship between us\Nis just not meant to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.58,0:13:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:823586,825054}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:825388,826922}You had too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.49,0:13:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:827490,828591}See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.59,0:13:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:828591,831260}Here comes the goddess savior\Nof the poor artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.56,0:13:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:834563,835765}Jules…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.84,0:14:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:853849,855284}Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.28,0:14:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:855284,856585}Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.58,0:14:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:856585,862258}That little boat is home to a family\Nwith God knows how many children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.99,0:14:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:866996,868531}Jules…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.53,0:14:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:868531,871067}Marry Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.06,0:14:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:871067,872134}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.13,0:14:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:872134,874770}Our relationship\Nis destined to fail, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.00,0:14:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:875004,877173}Why? Because our positions\Nare too different?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.17,0:14:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:877173,878874}The worlds we live in\Nare too far apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.87,0:14:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:878874,881243}I don't care about any of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.24,0:14:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:881243,883312}Jules, I care only about you—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.31,0:14:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:883312,887083}I only want you to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.51,0:14:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:889518,891821}Stop it! I'm so sick of others\Nmaking decisions for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.18,0:14:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:892188,893589}I am a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.58,0:14:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893589,896192}Do not decide for me\Nwhat my happiness is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.19,0:14:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:896192,898861}I decide my own happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.44,0:15:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:911440,914110}I want to live by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.11,0:15:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:914110,916145}I don't need anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.14,0:15:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:916145,918581}I'll throw everything else away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.88,0:15:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919882,921050}Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.95,0:15:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:921951,922985}Geneviève…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.95,0:15:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:924954,927723}I love you, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.72,0:15:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:927723,929225}Tell me not to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.70,0:15:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:941704,944440}Ms. Geneviève,\Nit is time to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.04,0:15:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:949044,953015}Tomorrow I will go\Nand tell your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.45,0:15:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:957453,958554}Then, I'll be on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:963058,964193}Promise you'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.02,0:16:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:965027,965795}I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.16,0:16:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:967163,969131}Mr. Gaston,\Nwhat happened here…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.13,0:16:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:969131,972802}I am Ms. Geneviève's\Nfaithful servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.00,0:16:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:978007,979942}{\i1}Goodbye, Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.17,0:16:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:980176,982878}{\i1}Jules… I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.85,0:16:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:987850,990486}{\i1}Farewell, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.76,0:16:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:998761,1002364}{\i1}"We'll never meet again".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.36,0:16:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1002364,1006735}{\i1}Jules vowed inwardly,\Nlooking at the departing carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.84,0:17:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1044840,1046242}{\i1}Forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.65,0:17:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1059655,1061123}{\i1}Forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.12,0:17:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1061123,1063359}{\i1}I have to forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1071500,1075204}{\i1}There are other things\Nthat I must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.20,0:17:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1075204,1076272}{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.73,0:17:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1076739,1079341}{\i1}We have to defend Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.34,0:18:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1079341,1080609}{\i1}I'll defend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.04,0:18:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1081043,1082878}{\i1}I'll defend Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.87,0:18:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1082878,1084880}{\i1}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.88,0:18:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1084880,1087283}{\i1}Defend Paris. Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.28,0:18:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1087283,1089018}{\i1}Defend Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.93,0:18:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1106936,1114176}It is very commendable that the citizens\Nof Paris are willing to take arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.17,0:18:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1114176,1118347}But I cannot say that\NI am really happy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.68,0:18:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1118681,1121984}What do you mean\Nby that, Mr. Thiers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.98,0:18:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1121984,1126889}When the city of Paris becomes\Na battlefield, there will be fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.88,0:18:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126889,1130292}This means risk for\Nour homes and properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.29,0:18:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1130292,1133262}We must use whatever means\Nnecessary to prevent this risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.92,0:18:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133929,1135664}Our homes and properties?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.66,0:19:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1135664,1141537}Surely you don't mean that to protect these,\Nwe should give up without a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.53,0:19:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1141537,1145007}That is also a possibility, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.00,0:19:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1145007,1146742}I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1146742,1148777}Paris is the pride of all of France!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.77,0:19:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148777,1152848}Losing Paris is equivalent\Nto losing the heart of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.84,0:19:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1152848,1155050}I will never agree to that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.95,0:19:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1162958,1165694}I can't believe this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.69,0:19:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1166695,1168197}What happened, Mr. General?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.43,0:19:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1168430,1169765}He's gone nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.76,0:19:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1169765,1176472}The politicians want to protect their assets\Nand consider selling Paris to Prussia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.20,0:19:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1177206,1178507}Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.50,0:19:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1178507,1179441}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.31,0:19:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1182311,1183679}Geneviève!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.67,0:19:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1183679,1185581}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.91,0:19:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1185914,1188884}I would like to talk\Nto Victor alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.81,0:19:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1189818,1194289}I don't mind, but don't abuse\Nyour privilege of being my sister too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.86,0:20:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1206869,1209772}What? You're not going\Nto Versailles? Geneviève…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.30,0:20:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1211306,1212107}I…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.04,0:20:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1213042,1214643}I…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.64,0:20:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1214643,1216245}I'm leaving our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.91,0:20:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1216912,1218814}Wait.\NWhat are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.04,0:20:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1219048,1220549}Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.54,0:20:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1220549,1222818}Please forgive me.\NBut my heart is with Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.93,0:20:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1237933,1238801}Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.33,0:20:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1239334,1242471}I am Victor Langlois\Nof the French Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1242471,1243105}Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.41,0:20:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1248410,1251113}Jules Francoeur, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.12,0:21:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1259121,1260522}I challenge you to a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.49,0:21:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270499,1272201}Marriage? With you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.63,0:21:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1273635,1276371}Naturally, not right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.37,0:21:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1276371,1278774}Just an engagement, for now.\NBut, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.77,0:21:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278774,1280142}Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.14,0:21:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1280142,1281877}I know we're\Nchildhood friends and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.87,0:21:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1281877,1284546}but how can you ask me\Nfor my hand so casually?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.88,0:21:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1284880,1288183}What? But this is\Nanything but casual.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1288183,1291253}I've asked you\Ncountless times, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.55,0:21:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1292554,1295290}Hey, when we grow up,\Nwe'll marry each other, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.29,0:21:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1295290,1298227}Nope. I'm not marrying\Nanyone like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.22,0:21:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1298227,1300763}Hey, when are we\Ngoing to marry?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.76,0:21:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1300763,1304399}Listen, I hate\Nweaklings and crybabies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.39,0:21:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1304399,1305734}Fine then!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.70,0:21:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1308704,1310205}What do you think\Nyou're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.30,0:21:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1313308,1315043}Oww!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.74,0:22:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1318747,1322417}Isabelle, your wedding dress\Nlooks so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.41,0:22:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1322417,1323886}Of course it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.88,0:22:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1323886,1327089}But you'll be disappointed,\Nsince I'll be wearing it for someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.95,0:22:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328957,1331393}No way… No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.63,0:22:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1339635,1345307}Do you remember that you\Neven agreed a few times?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.30,0:22:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1345307,1347676}I had to get rid of you somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.67,0:22:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1347676,1350546}Jean, stop living in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.54,0:22:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1350546,1352915}My answer is the same as before.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.91,0:22:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1352915,1354716}So you refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.15,0:22:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1355150,1356418}I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.41,0:22:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1356418,1357252}Come on…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.75,0:22:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1357753,1358353}Don't be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.35,0:22:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1358353,1359421}No means no!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.42,0:22:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1359421,1360222}– Come on…\N– Knock it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.52,0:22:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1362524,1364293}I will withdraw for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.29,0:22:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1364293,1367796}We're going to live next\Nto each other in Versailles, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.79,0:22:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1367796,1369565}I'll be able to see you any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.56,0:22:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1369565,1371767}Versailles is a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.76,0:22:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1371767,1373402}Without you, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.40,0:22:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1373402,1375637}Your words can't hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.63,0:22:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1375637,1377339}You silly girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.20,0:23:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1379208,1380342}Geneviève!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.97,0:23:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1381977,1383178}Where is Geneviève?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.38,0:23:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1385380,1387082}Do you need anything, Andréa?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.95,0:23:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1387950,1390485}Victor challenged\NJules to a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.07,0:23:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1416078,1420916}{\i1}Victor and Jules…\Nwill duel each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.91,0:23:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1420916,1425120}{\i1}It was something Isabelle\Ncould hardly even imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.65,0:23:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1426655,1432661}{\i1}The adult world began to appear\Nin vivid colors around the 15-old Isabelle.
