Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.26,0:24:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1440269,1443839}I'm overjoyed to see my brother\NAndréa return home in safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.83,0:24:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1443839,1448277}But Victor and Jules…\Nare going to fight in a duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.64,0:24:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1448644,1451647}Victor is a soldier.\NHe's an expert shooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.64,0:24:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1451647,1455083}But Jules?\NHe's just a piano teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.08,0:24:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1455083,1456618}What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.61,0:24:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1456618,1459688}In addition, there's also\Nthe evacuation to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.88,0:24:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1460889,1463525}Next time on "Isabelle from Paris":
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.52,0:24:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1463525,1467496}"On The Day of The Duel, The One I Love…"\NPlease look forward to it.
